title: Background task coder agents should support automatic follow-up review-and-fix passes

Background task coder agents should support automatic follow-up review-and-fix passes.

The background task/delegate system should be able to automatically run a follow-up review-and-fix step after implementation, using the same or a different agent/model. This should allow a coder agent to finish, then invoke a review/fix pass with acceptance criteria before the task is surfaced as complete. Consider integration with the existing review-and-fix skill/workflow, configurable reviewer runner/model, and clear status reporting through the background task lifecycle.
